The Hotel History

   Virginie Foucault and her brother Dominique, the fourth generation in a
   family of hoteliers, continue to practice the art of hospitality as
   their great-grandparents did at the start of the last century.
   The Hotel de l’Abeille has changed over the years, while retaining the
   warm and welcoming heart of a family business.


   More information

Llittle extra at L'Abeille

   Whether you are visiting our hotel on business or on holiday, you can
   enjoy: the tea room and bar, the library (access provided on request at
   reception), the seminar or reception rooms, the shop, the small gym and
   the roof garden with sunbathing in summer.


   More information
   Accueil

At the heart of Orléans, the Hotel de l’Abeille invites you to step inside
and join us on a journey through time, art and history.

   Experience love at first sight! The facade, a typical early 20th
   century design, offers a foretaste of the hotel's character. Step
   inside and you will discover a hotel-museum with elegant interiors,
   period furniture, antiques and a collection of art works devoted to
   Joan of Arc.

   Follow these sights by treating yourself to some “you time”. The garden
   terrace on the roof is an ideal spot to relax – a little cocoon of
   nature nestling above the town.
   Our hotel in Orléans is open all year round and is the perfect place to
   recharge your batteries. More than just a customer, here you will be
   welcomed as a guest of honour.


   Hôtel*** de l’Abeille - 64 rue Alsace Lorraine - 45000 Orléans - Tel :
   +33 (0)2 38 53 54 87 -
